{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This meeting has really been about a digital revolution,"},{"time":4000,"text":"but I'd like to argue that it's done; we won."},{"time":8000,"text":"We've had a digital revolution but we don't need to keep having it."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I'd like to look after that,"},{"time":14000,"text":"to look what comes after the digital revolution."},{"time":17000,"text":"So, let me start projecting forward."},{"time":19000,"text":"These are some projects I'm involved in today at MIT,"},{"time":23000,"text":"looking what comes after computers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"This first one, Internet Zero, up here -- this is a web server"},{"time":31000,"text":"that has the cost and complexity of an RFID tag --"},{"time":34000,"text":"about a dollar -- that can go in every light bulb and doorknob,"},{"time":37000,"text":"and this is getting commercialized very quickly."},{"time":39000,"text":"And what's interesting about it isn't the cost;"},{"time":41000,"text":"it's the way it encodes the Internet."},{"time":42000,"text":"It uses a kind of a Morse code for the Internet"},{"time":45000,"text":"so you could send it optically; you can communicate acoustically"},{"time":48000,"text":"through a power line, through RF."},{"time":50000,"text":"It takes the original principle of the Internet,"},{"time":52000,"text":"which is inter-networking computers,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and now lets devices inter-network."},{"time":57000,"text":"That we can take the whole idea that gave birth to the Internet"},{"time":60000,"text":"and bring it down to the physical world in this Internet Zero,"},{"time":63000,"text":"this internet of devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65000,"text":"So this is the next step from there to here,"},{"time":67000,"text":"and this is getting commercialized today."},{"time":70000,"text":"A step after that is a project on fungible computers."},{"time":75000,"text":"Fungible goods in economics can be extended and traded."},{"time":78000,"text":"So, half as much grain is half as much useful,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but half a baby or half a computer is less useful than"},{"time":83000,"text":"a whole baby or a whole computer,"},{"time":85000,"text":"and we've been trying to make computers that work that way."},{"time":88000,"text":"So, what you see in the background is a prototype."},{"time":90000,"text":"This was from a thesis of a student, Bill Butow, now at Intel,"},{"time":93000,"text":"who wondered why, instead of making bigger and bigger chips,"},{"time":96000,"text":"you don't make small chips, put them in a viscous medium,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and pour out computing by the pound or by the square inch."},{"time":101000,"text":"And that's what you see here."},{"time":103000,"text":"On the left was postscript being rendered by a conventional computer;"},{"time":106000,"text":"on the right is postscript being rendered from the first prototype"},{"time":109000,"text":"we made, but there's no frame buffer, IO processor,"},{"time":113000,"text":"any of that stuff -- it's just this material."},{"time":115000,"text":"Unlike this screen where the dots are placed carefully,"},{"time":117000,"text":"this is a raw material."},{"time":118000,"text":"If you add twice as much of it, you have twice as much display."},{"time":121000,"text":"If you shoot a gun through the middle, nothing happens."},{"time":124000,"text":"If you need more resource, you just apply more computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"So, that's the step after this -- of computing as a raw material."},{"time":131000,"text":"That's still conventional bits, the step after that is --"},{"time":134000,"text":"this is an earlier prototype in the lab;"},{"time":136000,"text":"this is high-speed video slowed down."},{"time":138000,"text":"Now, integrating chemistry in computation, where the bits are bubbles."},{"time":141000,"text":"This is showing making bits, this is showing --"},{"time":143000,"text":"once again, slowed down so you can see it,"},{"time":145000,"text":"bits interacting to do logic and multiplexing and de-multiplexing."},{"time":149000,"text":"So, now we can compute that the output arranges material"},{"time":152000,"text":"as well as information. And, ultimately, these are some slides"},{"time":156000,"text":"from an early project I did, computing where the bits are stored"},{"time":159000,"text":"quantum-mechanically in the nuclei of atoms, so"},{"time":162000,"text":"programs rearrange the nuclear structure of molecules."},{"time":166000,"text":"All of these are in the lab pushing further and further and further,"},{"time":170000,"text":"not as metaphor but literally integrating bits and atoms,"},{"time":173000,"text":"and they lead to the following recognition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"We all know we've had a digital revolution, but what is that?"},{"time":179000,"text":"Well, Shannon took us, in the '40s, from here to here:"},{"time":182000,"text":"from a telephone being a speaker wire that degraded with distance"},{"time":186000,"text":"to the Internet. And he proved the first threshold theorem, that shows"},{"time":190000,"text":"if you add information and remove it to a signal,"},{"time":193000,"text":"you can compute perfectly with an imperfect device."},{"time":195000,"text":"And that's when we got the Internet."},{"time":197000,"text":"Von Neumann, in the '50s, did the same thing for computing;"},{"time":200000,"text":"he showed you can have an unreliable computer but restore its state"},{"time":203000,"text":"to make it perfect. This was the last great analog computer at MIT:"},{"time":207000,"text":"a differential analyzer, and the more you ran it,"},{"time":209000,"text":"the worse the answer got."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"After Von Neumann, we have the Pentium, where the billionth transistor"},{"time":214000,"text":"is as reliable as the first one."},{"time":217000,"text":"But all our fabrication is down in this lower left corner."},{"time":220000,"text":"A state-of-the-art airplane factory rotating metal wax at fixed metal,"},{"time":223000,"text":"or you maybe melt some plastic. A 10-billion-dollar chip fab"},{"time":226000,"text":"uses a process a village artisan would recognize --"},{"time":229000,"text":"you spread stuff around and bake it."},{"time":232000,"text":"All the intelligence is external to the system;"},{"time":234000,"text":"the materials don't have information."},{"time":236000,"text":"Yesterday you heard about molecular biology,"},{"time":239000,"text":"which fundamentally computes to build."},{"time":241000,"text":"It's an information processing system."},{"time":243000,"text":"We've had digital revolutions in communication and computation,"},{"time":247000,"text":"but precisely the same idea, precisely the same math"},{"time":250000,"text":"Shannon and Von Neuman did, hasn't yet come out"},{"time":252000,"text":"to the physical world. So, inspired by that,"},{"time":255000,"text":"colleagues in this program -- the Center for Bits and Atoms"},{"time":257000,"text":"at MIT -- which is a group of people, like me,"},{"time":260000,"text":"who never understood the boundary between physical science"},{"time":263000,"text":"and computer science. I would even go further and say"},{"time":266000,"text":"computer science is one of the worst things that ever happened"},{"time":268000,"text":"to either computers or to science --"},{"time":270000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":271000,"text":"-- because the canon -- computer science --"},{"time":275000,"text":"many of them are great but the canon of computer science"},{"time":277000,"text":"prematurely froze a model of computation"},{"time":280000,"text":"based on technology that was available in 1950,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and nature's a much more powerful computer than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"So, you'll hear, tomorrow, from Saul Griffith. He was one of the"},{"time":289000,"text":"first students to emerge from this program."},{"time":292000,"text":"We started to figure out how you can compute to fabricate."},{"time":295000,"text":"This was just a proof of principle he did of tiles"},{"time":298000,"text":"that interact magnetically, where you write a code,"},{"time":300000,"text":"much like protein folding, that specifies their structure."},{"time":303000,"text":"So, there's no feedback to a tool metrology;"},{"time":306000,"text":"the material itself codes for its structure in just the same ways"},{"time":311000,"text":"that protein are fabricated. So, you can, for example, do that."},{"time":315000,"text":"You can do other things. That's in 2D. It works in 3D."},{"time":318000,"text":"The video on the upper right -- I won't show for time --"},{"time":320000,"text":"shows self-replication, templating so something can make something"},{"time":324000,"text":"that can make something, and we're doing that now over, maybe,"},{"time":327000,"text":"nine orders of magnitude. Those ideas have been used to show"},{"time":330000,"text":"the best fidelity and direct rate DNA to make an organism,"},{"time":333000,"text":"in functionalizing nanoclusters with peptide tails"},{"time":336000,"text":"that code for their assembly -- so, much like the magnets,"},{"time":338000,"text":"but now on nanometer scales."},{"time":340000,"text":"Laser micro-machining: essentially 3D printers that digitally fabricate"},{"time":344000,"text":"functional systems, all the way up to building buildings,"},{"time":347000,"text":"not by having blueprints,"},{"time":348000,"text":"but having the parts code for the structure of the building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"So, these are early examples in the lab of emerging technologies"},{"time":356000,"text":"to digitize fabrication. Computers that don't control tools"},{"time":360000,"text":"but computers that are tools, where the output of a program"},{"time":364000,"text":"rearranges atoms as well as bits."},{"time":368000,"text":"Now, to do that -- with your tax dollars, thank you --"},{"time":371000,"text":"I bought all these machines. We made a modest proposal"},{"time":375000,"text":"to the NSF. We wanted to be able to make anything on any length scale,"},{"time":379000,"text":"all in one place, because you can't segregate digital fabrication"},{"time":383000,"text":"by a discipline or a length scale."},{"time":385000,"text":"So we put together focused nano beam writers"},{"time":389000,"text":"and supersonic water jet cutters and excimer micro-machining systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"But I had a problem. Once I had all these machines,"},{"time":397000,"text":"I was spending too much time teaching students to use them."},{"time":400000,"text":"So I started teaching a class, modestly called,"},{"time":402000,"text":"\"How To Make Almost Anything.\" And that wasn't meant to be provocative;"},{"time":405000,"text":"it was just for a few research students."},{"time":407000,"text":"But the first day of class looked like this."},{"time":409000,"text":"You know, hundreds of people came in begging,"},{"time":411000,"text":"all my life I've been waiting for this class; I'll do anything to do it."},{"time":414000,"text":"Then they'd ask, can you teach it at MIT? It seems too useful?"},{"time":417000,"text":"And then the next --"},{"time":418000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":420000,"text":"-- surprising thing was they weren't there to do research."},{"time":421000,"text":"They were there because they wanted to make stuff."},{"time":423000,"text":"They had no conventional technical background."},{"time":427000,"text":"At the end of a semester they integrated their skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"I'll show an old video. Kelly was a sculptor, and this is what she did"},{"time":433000,"text":"with her semester project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"(Video): Kelly: Hi, I'm Kelly and this is my scream buddy."},{"time":440000,"text":"Do you ever find yourself in a situation"},{"time":443000,"text":"where you really have to scream, but you can't because you're at work,"},{"time":448000,"text":"or you're in a classroom, or you're watching your children,"},{"time":451000,"text":"or you're in any number of situations where it's just not permitted?"},{"time":456000,"text":"Well, scream buddy is a portable space for screaming."},{"time":460000,"text":"When a user screams into scream buddy, their scream is silenced."},{"time":465000,"text":"It is also recorded for later release where, when and how"},{"time":469000,"text":"the user chooses."},{"time":491000,"text":"(Scream)"},{"time":494000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"So, Einstein would like this."},{"time":500000,"text":"This student made a web browser for parrots --"},{"time":501000,"text":"lets parrots surf the Net and talk to other parrots."},{"time":504000,"text":"This student's made an alarm clock you wrestle"},{"time":506000,"text":"to prove you're awake; this is one that defends --"},{"time":508000,"text":"a dress that defends your personal space."},{"time":510000,"text":"This isn't technology for communication;"},{"time":512000,"text":"it's technology to prevent it."},{"time":514000,"text":"This is a device that lets you see your music."},{"time":517000,"text":"This is a student who made a machine that makes machines,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and he made it by making Lego bricks that do the computing."},{"time":523000,"text":"Just year after year -- and I finally realized"},{"time":525000,"text":"the students were showing the killer app of personal fabrication"},{"time":529000,"text":"is products for a market of one person."},{"time":531000,"text":"You don't need this for what you can get in Wal-Mart;"},{"time":533000,"text":"you need this for what makes you unique."},{"time":534000,"text":"Ken Olsen famously said, nobody needs a computer in the home."},{"time":538000,"text":"But you don't use it for inventory and payroll;"},{"time":540000,"text":"DEC is now twice bankrupt. You don't need personal fabrication"},{"time":543000,"text":"in the home to buy what you can buy because you can buy it."},{"time":545000,"text":"You need it for what makes you unique, just like personalization."},{"time":549000,"text":"So, with that, in turn, 20 million dollars today does this;"},{"time":553000,"text":"20 years from now we'll make Star Trek replicators that make anything."},{"time":557000,"text":"The students hijacked all the machines I bought to do personal fabrication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"Today, when you spend that much of your money,"},{"time":563000,"text":"there's a government requirement to do outreach, which often means"},{"time":566000,"text":"classes at a local school, a website -- stuff that's just not that exciting."},{"time":569000,"text":"So, I made a deal with my NSF program managers that"},{"time":573000,"text":"instead of talking about it, I'd give people the tools."},{"time":575000,"text":"This wasn't meant to be provocative or important,"},{"time":577000,"text":"but we put together these Fab Labs. It's about 20,000 dollars in equipment"},{"time":581000,"text":"that approximate both what the 20 million dollars does and where it's going."},{"time":586000,"text":"A laser cutter to do press-fit assembly with 3D from 2D,"},{"time":589000,"text":"a sign cutter to plot in copper to do electromagnetics,"},{"time":591000,"text":"a micron scale,"},{"time":593000,"text":"numerically-controlled milling machine for precise structures,"},{"time":595000,"text":"programming tools for less than a dollar,"},{"time":598000,"text":"100-nanosecond microcontrollers. It lets you work from microns"},{"time":601000,"text":"and microseconds on up, and they exploded around the world."},{"time":605000,"text":"This wasn't scheduled, but they went from inner-city Boston"},{"time":607000,"text":"to Pobal in India, to Secondi-Takoradi on Ghana's coast"},{"time":611000,"text":"to Soshanguve in a township in South Africa,"},{"time":614000,"text":"to the far north of Norway, uncovering, or helping uncover,"},{"time":618000,"text":"for all the attention to the digital divide,"},{"time":621000,"text":"we would find unused computers in all these places."},{"time":625000,"text":"A farmer in a rural village -- a kid needs to measure and modify"},{"time":628000,"text":"the world, not just get information about it on a screen."},{"time":632000,"text":"That there's really a fabrication and an instrumentation divide"},{"time":634000,"text":"bigger than the digital divide."},{"time":637000,"text":"And the way you close it is not IT for the masses but IT development for the masses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"So, in place after place"},{"time":643000,"text":"we saw this same progression: that we'd open one of these Fab Labs,"},{"time":646000,"text":"where we didn't -- this is too crazy to think of."},{"time":649000,"text":"We didn't think this up, that we would get pulled to these places;"},{"time":652000,"text":"we'd open it. The first step was just empowerment."},{"time":654000,"text":"You can see it in their face, just this joy of, I can do it."},{"time":657000,"text":"This is a girl in inner-city Boston who had just done a high-tech"},{"time":659000,"text":"on-demand craft sale in the inner city community center."},{"time":663000,"text":"It goes on from there to serious hands-on technical education"},{"time":667000,"text":"informally, out of schools. In Ghana we had set up one of these labs."},{"time":672000,"text":"We designed a network sensor, and kids would show up"},{"time":674000,"text":"and refuse to leave the lab."},{"time":675000,"text":"There was a girl who insisted we stay late at night --"},{"time":678000,"text":"(Video): Kids: I love the Fab Lab."},{"time":680000,"text":"-- her first night in the lab because she was going to make the sensor."},{"time":683000,"text":"So she insisted on fabbing the board, learning how to stuff it,"},{"time":686000,"text":"learning how to program it. She didn't really know"},{"time":688000,"text":"what she was doing or why she was doing it, but she knew"},{"time":690000,"text":"she just had to do it. There was something electric about it."},{"time":693000,"text":"This is late at, you know, 11 o'clock at night"},{"time":695000,"text":"and I think I was the only person surprised when what she built"},{"time":698000,"text":"worked the first time."},{"time":700000,"text":"And I've shown this to engineers at big companies, and they say"},{"time":702000,"text":"they can't do this. Any one thing she's doing, they can do better,"},{"time":705000,"text":"but it's distributed over many people and many sites"},{"time":708000,"text":"and they can't do in an afternoon"},{"time":709000,"text":"what this little girl in rural Ghana is doing."},{"time":728000,"text":"(Video): Girl: My name is Valentina Kofi; I am eight years old."},{"time":732000,"text":"I made a stacking board."},{"time":735000,"text":"And, again, that was just for the joy of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"Then these labs started doing serious problem solving --"},{"time":741000,"text":"instrumentation for agriculture in India,"},{"time":743000,"text":"steam turbines for energy conversion in Ghana,"},{"time":745000,"text":"high-gain antennas in thin client computers."},{"time":749000,"text":"And then, in turn, businesses started to grow,"},{"time":750000,"text":"like making these antennas."},{"time":751000,"text":"And finally, the lab started doing invention."},{"time":753000,"text":"We're learning more from them than we're giving them."},{"time":755000,"text":"I was showing my kids in a Fab Lab how to use it."},{"time":758000,"text":"They invented a way to do a construction kit out of a cardboard box --"},{"time":762000,"text":"which, as you see up there, that's becoming a business --"},{"time":764000,"text":"but their design was better than Saul's design at MIT,"},{"time":767000,"text":"so there's now three students at MIT doing their theses on"},{"time":770000,"text":"scaling the work of eight-year-old children"},{"time":773000,"text":"because they had better designs."},{"time":774000,"text":"Real invention is happening in these labs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777000,"text":"And I still kept -- so, in the last year I've been spending time with"},{"time":779000,"text":"heads of state and generals and tribal chiefs who all want this,"},{"time":782000,"text":"and I keep saying, but this isn't the real thing."},{"time":784000,"text":"Wait, like, 20 years and then we'll be done."},{"time":786000,"text":"And I finally got what's been going on. This is Kernigan and Ritchie"},{"time":789000,"text":"inventing UNIX on a PDP."},{"time":792000,"text":"PDPs came between mainframes and minicomputers."},{"time":794000,"text":"They were tens of thousands of dollars, hard to use,"},{"time":797000,"text":"but they brought computing down to work groups,"},{"time":799000,"text":"and everything we do today happened there."},{"time":801000,"text":"These Fab Labs are the cost and complexity of a PDP."},{"time":804000,"text":"The projection of digital fabrication"},{"time":806000,"text":"isn't a projection for the future; we are now in the PDP era."},{"time":809000,"text":"We talked in hushed tones about the great discoveries then."},{"time":812000,"text":"It was very chaotic, it wasn't, sort of, clear what was going on."},{"time":815000,"text":"In the same sense we are now, today, in the minicomputer era"},{"time":818000,"text":"of digital fabrication."},{"time":820000,"text":"The only problem with that is it breaks everybody's boundaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824000,"text":"In DC, I go to every agency that wants to talk, you know;"},{"time":827000,"text":"in the Bay Area, I go to every organization you can think of --"},{"time":829000,"text":"they all want to talk about it, but it breaks"},{"time":831000,"text":"their organizational boundaries. In fact, it's illegal for them,"},{"time":834000,"text":"in many cases, to equip ordinary people to create"},{"time":838000,"text":"rather than consume technology."},{"time":839000,"text":"And that problem is so severe that the ultimate invention"},{"time":843000,"text":"coming from this community surprised me:"},{"time":846000,"text":"it's the social engineering. That the lab in far north of Norway --"},{"time":850000,"text":"this is so far north its satellite dishes look at the ground"},{"time":852000,"text":"rather than the sky because that's where the satellites are --"},{"time":856000,"text":"the lab outgrew the little barn that it was in."},{"time":857000,"text":"It was there because they wanted to find animals in the mountains"},{"time":860000,"text":"but it outgrew it, so they built this extraordinary village for the lab."},{"time":864000,"text":"This isn't a university; it's not a company. It's essentially"},{"time":866000,"text":"a village for invention; it's a village for the outliers in society,"},{"time":871000,"text":"and those have been growing up around these Fab Labs"},{"time":873000,"text":"all around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"So this program has split into an NGO foundation,"},{"time":878000,"text":"a Fab Foundation to support the scaling, a micro VC fund."},{"time":882000,"text":"The person who runs it nicely describes it as"},{"time":883000,"text":"\"machines that make machines need businesses that make businesses:\""},{"time":887000,"text":"it's a cross between micro-finance and VC to do fan-out,"},{"time":890000,"text":"and then the research partnerships back at MIT for what's"},{"time":892000,"text":"making it possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"So I'd like to leave you with two thoughts."},{"time":897000,"text":"There's been a sea change in aid, from top-down mega-projects"},{"time":902000,"text":"to bottom-up, grassroots, micro-finance investing in the roots,"},{"time":906000,"text":"so that everybody's got that that's what works."},{"time":909000,"text":"But we still look at technology as top-down mega-projects."},{"time":912000,"text":"Computing, communication, energy for the rest of the planet"},{"time":915000,"text":"are these top-down mega-projects."},{"time":917000,"text":"If this room full of heroes is just clever enough,"},{"time":919000,"text":"you can solve the problems."},{"time":921000,"text":"The message coming from the Fab Labs is that"},{"time":923000,"text":"the other five billion people on the planet"},{"time":925000,"text":"aren't just technical sinks; they're sources."},{"time":927000,"text":"The real opportunity is to harness the inventive power of the world"},{"time":930000,"text":"to locally design and produce solutions to local problems."},{"time":934000,"text":"I thought that's the projection 20 years hence into the future,"},{"time":937000,"text":"but it's where we are today."},{"time":939000,"text":"It breaks every organizational boundary we can think of."},{"time":941000,"text":"The hardest thing at this point is the social engineering"},{"time":944000,"text":"and the organizational engineering, but it's here today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947000,"text":"And, finally, any talk like this on the future of computing"},{"time":949000,"text":"is required to show Moore's law, but my favorite version --"},{"time":953000,"text":"this is Gordon Moore's original one from his original paper --"},{"time":958000,"text":"and what's happened is, year after year after year,"},{"time":960000,"text":"we've scaled and we've scaled and we've scaled"},{"time":961000,"text":"and we've scaled, and we've scaled and we've scaled,"},{"time":965000,"text":"and we've scaled and we've scaled,"},{"time":966000,"text":"and there's this looming bug of what's going to happen"},{"time":968000,"text":"at the end of Moore's law; this ultimate bug is coming."},{"time":972000,"text":"But we're coming to appreciate, is the transition from 2D to 3D,"},{"time":977000,"text":"from programming bits to programming atoms,"},{"time":980000,"text":"turns the ends of Moore's law scaling from the ultimate bug"},{"time":982000,"text":"to the ultimate feature."},{"time":984000,"text":"So, we're just at the edge of this digital revolution in fabrication,"},{"time":988000,"text":"where the output of computation programs the physical world."},{"time":991000,"text":"So, together, these two projects answer questions"},{"time":994000,"text":"I hadn't asked carefully. The class at MIT shows the killer app"},{"time":998000,"text":"for personal fabrication in the developed world"},{"time":1000000,"text":"is technology for a market of one: personal expression in technology"},{"time":1004000,"text":"that touches a passion unlike anything I've seen in technology"},{"time":1007000,"text":"for a very long time."},{"time":1009000,"text":"And the killer app for the rest of the planet is the instrumentation"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and the fabrication divide: people locally developing solutions"},{"time":1016000,"text":"to local problems. Thank you."}]}]}